    <item>
      <title>Language Overview</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/overview/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;language-overview&#34;&gt;Language Overview&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;FQL is the language used by Ferret to describe data extraction, transformation, automation, and runtime-driven workflows.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;At a high level, FQL scripts take input from somewhere, shape it into useful values, and return structured results.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;That input might be simple in-memory data:&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-horizontal is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-editor-1-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-header&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.fql&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;small&gt;Ferret v2&lt;/small&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-toggle-button&#34; class=&#34;button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34; aria-expanded=&#34;false&#34; aria-controls=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34;&gt;Output&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-run-button&#34; class=&#34;run button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34;&gt;Run&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-progress&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-progress&#34; role=&#34;progressbar&#34; aria-label=&#34;Running query&#34; hidden&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;span id=&#34;code-editor-1-run-status&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-sr-only&#34; aria-live=&#34;polite&#34; aria-atomic=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-grid&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-grid&#34; style=&#34;grid-template-columns: 1fr;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-source-pane&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane code-editor-pane-source&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;query.fql&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;FQL&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;LET user = {&#xA;    name: &amp;#34;Ada&amp;#34;,&#xA;    roles: [&amp;#34;admin&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;editor&amp;#34;]&#xA;}&#xA;&#xA;RETURN {&#xA;    name: user.name,&#xA;    isAdmin: CONTAINS(user.roles, &amp;#34;admin&amp;#34;)&#xA;}&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane code-editor-pane-result&#34; hidden&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;result.json&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                        &lt;span&gt;output&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                        &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-close-button&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34; aria-controls=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34;&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-result&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-result&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            function createEditor(id, mode, useWorker) {&#xA;                const editor = ace.edit(id);&#xA;                editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;                editor.session.setUseWorker(useWorker);&#xA;                editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + mode);&#xA;                editor.setOptions({&#xA;                    displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                    printMargin: false&#xA;                });&#xA;&#xA;                return editor;&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            const btn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-run-button&#39;);&#xA;            const textEditor = createEditor(&#39;code-editor-1-text&#39;, &#39;fql&#39;, true);&#xA;            const resultEditor = createEditor(&#39;code-editor-1-result&#39;, &#39;json&#39;, false);&#xA;            resultEditor.setReadOnly(true);&#xA;            const resultExpandBtn = null;&#xA;            const editorHeader = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-header&#39;);&#xA;            const editorGrid = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-grid&#39;);&#xA;            const runProgress = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-progress&#39;);&#xA;            const runStatus = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-run-status&#39;);&#xA;            const resultPane = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-pane&#39;);&#xA;            const resultToggleBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-toggle-button&#39;);&#xA;            const resultCloseBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-close-button&#39;);&#xA;            let isResultVisible = !resultPane.hidden;&#xA;&#xA;            function resetResultExpansion() {&#xA;                if (!resultExpandBtn) {&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                isResultExpanded = false;&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.textContent = &#39;Expand&#39;;&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function syncEditorLayout() {&#xA;                const sourceHeight = getEditorContentHeight(textEditor);&#xA;                textEditor.container.style.height = `${sourceHeight}px`;&#xA;&#xA;                if (isResultVisible) {&#xA;                    const resultHeight = getEditorContentHeight(resultEditor);&#xA;                    applyResultHeight(resultHeight);&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                textEditor.resize();&#xA;&#xA;                if (isResultVisible) {&#xA;                    resultEditor.resize();&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function setResultVisible(nextVisible) {&#xA;                isResultVisible = nextVisible;&#xA;                resultPane.hidden = !nextVisible;&#xA;                resultToggleBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, nextVisible ? &#39;true&#39; : &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.style.gridTemplateColumns = nextVisible ? &#39;&#39; : &#39;1fr&#39;;&#xA;&#xA;                if (!nextVisible) {&#xA;                    resetResultExpansion();&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                window.requestAnimationFrame(() =&gt; {&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                    resultEditor.resize(true);&#xA;                });&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            resultToggleBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                setResultVisible(!isResultVisible);&#xA;            });&#xA;&#xA;            resultCloseBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                setResultVisible(false);&#xA;            });&#xA;            const collapsedResultHeightStyle = resultEditor.container.style.height;&#xA;            let isResultExpanded = false;&#xA;&#xA;            function getEditorContentHeight(editor) {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getMaxResultHeight(fallbackHeight) {&#xA;                const viewportHeight = window.innerHeight || document.documentElement.clientHeight || fallbackHeight;&#xA;                const rootFontSize = parseFloat(window.getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).fontSize) || 16;&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.min(viewportHeight * 0.45, 32 * rootFontSize);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getCollapsedResultHeight() {&#xA;                return getEditorContentHeight(resultEditor);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getExpandedResultHeight(collapsedHeight) {&#xA;                const lineHeight = resultEditor.renderer.lineHeight || textEditor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const maxAllowedHeight = getMaxResultHeight(collapsedHeight);&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(resultEditor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const contentHeight = (screenLines * lineHeight) + (lineHeight * 2);&#xA;                const targetHeight = Math.min(contentHeight, maxAllowedHeight);&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.max(collapsedHeight, Math.round(targetHeight));&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function applyResultHeight(collapsedHeight) {&#xA;                if (resultExpandBtn &amp;&amp; isResultExpanded) {&#xA;                    resultEditor.container.style.height = `${getExpandedResultHeight(collapsedHeight)}px`;&#xA;                } else {&#xA;                    resultEditor.container.style.height = `${Math.min(collapsedHeight, getMaxResultHeight(collapsedHeight))}px`;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                resultEditor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;            textEditor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, syncEditorLayout);&#xA;&#xA;            if (resultExpandBtn) {&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                    isResultExpanded = !isResultExpanded;&#xA;                    resultExpandBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, isResultExpanded ? &#39;true&#39; : &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                    resultExpandBtn.textContent = isResultExpanded ? &#39;Collapse&#39; : &#39;Expand&#39;;&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                });&#xA;            }&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, syncEditorLayout);&#xA;            syncEditorLayout();&#xA;&#xA;            function setContent(editor, content) {&#xA;                editor.setValue(content, -1);&#xA;            }&#xA;                const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;                function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                    copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                    copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                    copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                    if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                        throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                    }&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                    if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                        return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                        });&#xA;                    }&#xA;&#xA;                    copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                    return Promise.resolve();&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                    copyTextToClipboard(textEditor.getValue())&#xA;                        .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                            window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                                copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                            }, 1200);&#xA;                        })&#xA;                        .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                            console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                            console.error(err);&#xA;                        });&#xA;                });&#xA;&#xA;            let isRunning = false;&#xA;&#xA;            function onStart() {&#xA;                isRunning = true;&#xA;                textEditor.setReadOnly(true);&#xA;                runProgress.hidden = false;&#xA;                runStatus.textContent = &#39;Running query&#39;;&#xA;                editorHeader.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;                btn.classList.add(&#39;is-loading&#39;);&#xA;                btn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function onEnd(result) {&#xA;                isRunning = false;&#xA;                textEditor.setReadOnly(false);&#xA;                runProgress.hidden = true;&#xA;                runStatus.textContent = &#39;&#39;;&#xA;                editorHeader.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                btn.classList.remove(&#39;is-loading&#39;);&#xA;                btn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;                setContent(resultEditor, result);&#xA;                setResultVisible(true);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            btn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                if (isRunning) {&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                const body = {&#xA;                        text: textEditor.getValue(),&#xA;                        params: JSON.parse(&#34;{}&#34;)&#xA;                };&#xA;                const url = &#34;https:\/\/worker-v2-811908774949.us-east1.run.app&#34;;&#xA;&#xA;                onStart();&#xA;                fetch(url, {&#xA;                    method: &#39;post&#39;,&#xA;                    cache: &#39;no-cache&#39;,&#xA;                    headers: {&#xA;                        &#39;Content-Type&#39;: &#39;application/json; charset=utf-8&#39;&#xA;                    },&#xA;                    signal: AbortSignal.timeout(1000 * 60), &#xA;                    body: JSON.stringify(body)&#xA;                })&#xA;                    .then(r =&gt; {&#xA;                        if (r.status === 200) {&#xA;                            return r.json()&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        if (r.status === 426) {&#xA;                            throw new Error(`Too many requests. Try again later.`);&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        if (r.status === 400) {&#xA;                            return r.json().then((data) =&gt; {&#xA;                                if (data.details) {&#xA;                                    throw new Error(data.details);&#xA;                                }&#xA;                                &#xA;                                throw new Error(data.error);&#xA;                            });&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        throw new Error(`Unexpected error. Try again later.`);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .then((data) =&gt; {&#xA;                        onEnd(JSON.stringify(data, null, 4));&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        onEnd(err.message);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Syntax</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/syntax/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/syntax/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;script-structure&#34;&gt;Script Structure&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;FQL is Ferret&amp;rsquo;s query and automation language. It is used to describe data extraction, transformation, testing, and automation workflows that can run from the Ferret CLI, from a host application, from tests, or inside a runtime that provides extra capabilities such as HTML, browser, network, or event support.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;An FQL script is a sequence of statements that produce a final value.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Most scripts follow a simple shape:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;declare or receive input&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;transform data&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;return a result&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-horizontal is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-header&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.fql&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;small&gt;Ferret v2&lt;/small&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-toggle-button&#34; class=&#34;button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34; aria-expanded=&#34;false&#34; aria-controls=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34;&gt;Output&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-run-button&#34; class=&#34;run button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34;&gt;Run&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-progress&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-progress&#34; role=&#34;progressbar&#34; aria-label=&#34;Running query&#34; hidden&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;span id=&#34;code-editor-1-run-status&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-sr-only&#34; aria-live=&#34;polite&#34; aria-atomic=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-grid&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-grid&#34; style=&#34;grid-template-columns: 1fr;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-source-pane&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane code-editor-pane-source&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;query.fql&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;FQL&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;LET user = {&#xA;    name: &amp;#34;Ada&amp;#34;,&#xA;    roles: [&amp;#34;admin&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;editor&amp;#34;]&#xA;}&#xA;&#xA;LET isAdmin = CONTAINS(user.roles, &amp;#34;admin&amp;#34;)&#xA;&#xA;RETURN {&#xA;    name: user.name,&#xA;    isAdmin: isAdmin&#xA;}&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane code-editor-pane-result&#34; hidden&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;span&gt;result.json&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane-header-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                        &lt;span&gt;output&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                        &lt;button id=&#34;code-editor-1-result-close-button&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-pane-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34; aria-controls=&#34;code-editor-1-result-pane&#34;&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;                &lt;div id=&#34;code-editor-1-result&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-result&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            function createEditor(id, mode, useWorker) {&#xA;                const editor = ace.edit(id);&#xA;                editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;                editor.session.setUseWorker(useWorker);&#xA;                editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + mode);&#xA;                editor.setOptions({&#xA;                    displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                    printMargin: false&#xA;                });&#xA;&#xA;                return editor;&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            const btn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-run-button&#39;);&#xA;            const textEditor = createEditor(&#39;code-editor-1-text&#39;, &#39;fql&#39;, true);&#xA;            const resultEditor = createEditor(&#39;code-editor-1-result&#39;, &#39;json&#39;, false);&#xA;            resultEditor.setReadOnly(true);&#xA;            const resultExpandBtn = null;&#xA;            const editorHeader = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-header&#39;);&#xA;            const editorGrid = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-grid&#39;);&#xA;            const runProgress = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-progress&#39;);&#xA;            const runStatus = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-run-status&#39;);&#xA;            const resultPane = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-pane&#39;);&#xA;            const resultToggleBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-toggle-button&#39;);&#xA;            const resultCloseBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-editor-1-result-close-button&#39;);&#xA;            let isResultVisible = !resultPane.hidden;&#xA;&#xA;            function resetResultExpansion() {&#xA;                if (!resultExpandBtn) {&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                isResultExpanded = false;&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.textContent = &#39;Expand&#39;;&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function syncEditorLayout() {&#xA;                const sourceHeight = getEditorContentHeight(textEditor);&#xA;                textEditor.container.style.height = `${sourceHeight}px`;&#xA;&#xA;                if (isResultVisible) {&#xA;                    const resultHeight = getEditorContentHeight(resultEditor);&#xA;                    applyResultHeight(resultHeight);&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                textEditor.resize();&#xA;&#xA;                if (isResultVisible) {&#xA;                    resultEditor.resize();&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function setResultVisible(nextVisible) {&#xA;                isResultVisible = nextVisible;&#xA;                resultPane.hidden = !nextVisible;&#xA;                resultToggleBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, nextVisible ? &#39;true&#39; : &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.style.gridTemplateColumns = nextVisible ? &#39;&#39; : &#39;1fr&#39;;&#xA;&#xA;                if (!nextVisible) {&#xA;                    resetResultExpansion();&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                window.requestAnimationFrame(() =&gt; {&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                    resultEditor.resize(true);&#xA;                });&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            resultToggleBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                setResultVisible(!isResultVisible);&#xA;            });&#xA;&#xA;            resultCloseBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                setResultVisible(false);&#xA;            });&#xA;            const collapsedResultHeightStyle = resultEditor.container.style.height;&#xA;            let isResultExpanded = false;&#xA;&#xA;            function getEditorContentHeight(editor) {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getMaxResultHeight(fallbackHeight) {&#xA;                const viewportHeight = window.innerHeight || document.documentElement.clientHeight || fallbackHeight;&#xA;                const rootFontSize = parseFloat(window.getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).fontSize) || 16;&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.min(viewportHeight * 0.45, 32 * rootFontSize);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getCollapsedResultHeight() {&#xA;                return getEditorContentHeight(resultEditor);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function getExpandedResultHeight(collapsedHeight) {&#xA;                const lineHeight = resultEditor.renderer.lineHeight || textEditor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const maxAllowedHeight = getMaxResultHeight(collapsedHeight);&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(resultEditor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const contentHeight = (screenLines * lineHeight) + (lineHeight * 2);&#xA;                const targetHeight = Math.min(contentHeight, maxAllowedHeight);&#xA;&#xA;                return Math.max(collapsedHeight, Math.round(targetHeight));&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function applyResultHeight(collapsedHeight) {&#xA;                if (resultExpandBtn &amp;&amp; isResultExpanded) {&#xA;                    resultEditor.container.style.height = `${getExpandedResultHeight(collapsedHeight)}px`;&#xA;                } else {&#xA;                    resultEditor.container.style.height = `${Math.min(collapsedHeight, getMaxResultHeight(collapsedHeight))}px`;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                resultEditor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;            textEditor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, syncEditorLayout);&#xA;&#xA;            if (resultExpandBtn) {&#xA;                resultExpandBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                    isResultExpanded = !isResultExpanded;&#xA;                    resultExpandBtn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-expanded&#39;, isResultExpanded ? &#39;true&#39; : &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                    resultExpandBtn.textContent = isResultExpanded ? &#39;Collapse&#39; : &#39;Expand&#39;;&#xA;                    syncEditorLayout();&#xA;                });&#xA;            }&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, syncEditorLayout);&#xA;            syncEditorLayout();&#xA;&#xA;            function setContent(editor, content) {&#xA;                editor.setValue(content, -1);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            let isRunning = false;&#xA;&#xA;            function onStart() {&#xA;                isRunning = true;&#xA;                textEditor.setReadOnly(true);&#xA;                runProgress.hidden = false;&#xA;                runStatus.textContent = &#39;Running query&#39;;&#xA;                editorHeader.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;                btn.classList.add(&#39;is-loading&#39;);&#xA;                btn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;true&#39;);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function onEnd(result) {&#xA;                isRunning = false;&#xA;                textEditor.setReadOnly(false);&#xA;                runProgress.hidden = true;&#xA;                runStatus.textContent = &#39;&#39;;&#xA;                editorHeader.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                editorGrid.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;                btn.classList.remove(&#39;is-loading&#39;);&#xA;                btn.setAttribute(&#39;aria-busy&#39;, &#39;false&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;                setContent(resultEditor, result);&#xA;                setResultVisible(true);&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            btn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                if (isRunning) {&#xA;                    return;&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                const body = {&#xA;                        text: textEditor.getValue(),&#xA;                        params: JSON.parse(&#34;{}&#34;)&#xA;                };&#xA;                const url = &#34;https:\/\/worker-v2-811908774949.us-east1.run.app&#34;;&#xA;&#xA;                onStart();&#xA;                fetch(url, {&#xA;                    method: &#39;post&#39;,&#xA;                    cache: &#39;no-cache&#39;,&#xA;                    headers: {&#xA;                        &#39;Content-Type&#39;: &#39;application/json; charset=utf-8&#39;&#xA;                    },&#xA;                    signal: AbortSignal.timeout(1000 * 60), &#xA;                    body: JSON.stringify(body)&#xA;                })&#xA;                    .then(r =&gt; {&#xA;                        if (r.status === 200) {&#xA;                            return r.json()&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        if (r.status === 426) {&#xA;                            throw new Error(`Too many requests. Try again later.`);&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        if (r.status === 400) {&#xA;                            return r.json().then((data) =&gt; {&#xA;                                if (data.details) {&#xA;                                    throw new Error(data.details);&#xA;                                }&#xA;                                &#xA;                                throw new Error(data.error);&#xA;                            });&#xA;                        }&#xA;                        &#xA;                        throw new Error(`Unexpected error. Try again later.`);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .then((data) =&gt; {&#xA;                        onEnd(JSON.stringify(data, null, 4));&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        onEnd(err.message);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The final value may be produced by a top-level &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt;, or by another terminal statement such as a top-level &lt;code&gt;FOR&lt;/code&gt; block.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bind Parameters</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/parameters/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/parameters/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;bind-parameters&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#bind-parameters&#34;&gt;&#xA;Bind parameters&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;FQL supports the usage of bind parameters, thus allowing to separate the query text from literal values used in the query. It is good practice to separate the query text from the literal values because it allows to reuse same query in different scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using bind parameters, the meaning of an existing query cannot be changed. Bind parameters can be used everywhere in a query where literals can be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Type Ordering</title>
